According to 29 CFR 1910.302(a)(1), the design safety standards for electric utilization systems (found in §§1910.302 through 1910.308) cover electrical installations and utilization equipment installed or used within or on buildings, structures, and other premises [1]. Beyond permanent buildings, the specific types of installations explicitly covered include:

*   Yards [1];
*   Carnivals [1];
*   Parking and other lots [1];
*   Mobile homes [1];
*   Recreational vehicles [1];
*   Industrial substations [1];
*   Conductors that connect the installations to a supply of electricity [1]; and
*   Other outside conductors on the premises [1].
